Key Match Events: Mitchell scored 30 points including a jumper with three-tenths of a second left
Lillard had 41 points with nine assists and shot 10 of 15 from 3-point range
Lillard hit a step-back jumper with 9.8 seconds remaining to put Milwaukee ahead
Cleveland called timeout, Mitchell caught a pass from Evan Mobley, dribbled inside the arc and hit a 19-footer
Post-Match Reflections: The 7-0 Cavaliers are one win away from matching their best start in franchise history
Cleveland showed its gumption by winning at less than full strength
Milwaukee has lost five straight since winning its opener
The Bucks need more from Gary Trent Jr., who scored three points in 34 minutes
Miscellaneous Highlights: Milwaukee played without Khris Middleton, who hasn't yet made his season debut as he recovers from surgery on his ankles
Giannis Antetokounmpo had 34 points, 16 rebounds and nine assists for the Bucks
